cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.BI, cs.IT, cs.MS 

The paper discusses the development of an interface between molecular nanonetworks and electromagnetic networks, which involves the use of biosensors and signal transduction. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for the modeling aspect, cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) for the use of biosensors, cs.BI (Bioinformatics) for the focus on the medical domain, cs.IT (Information Theory) for the communication aspect, and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) for the development of deterministic and noise models.
